gomodel:SYNGO_1634  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The supplemental table S1 contains proteins identified in the PSD preparation (Synaptic junctional protein preparation).\nFor proteins coming from datasets derived from PSD (detergent-resistant synaptic junctions) preparations without defined selection / enrichment of the pre- or postsynaptic compartment we cannot assign these proteins to excitatory and/or inhibitory nor to the presynapse or / and postsynapse without further information.\n\n13/10/2017 Pim\n- Listed as 60S ribosomal protein L4 in Table S1. Experimental description: Briefly adult mouse brains (2-16 months, 20 animals, 10 g wet weight) were homogenized ... p. 915" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
